  <my:Hazards>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="1">
      <my:Description>Electricity</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Safe Work Permit should be issued; 
b) Use of PPE; 
c) Use of dry insulation mat; 
d) Before any work is done fuses should be removed or ensure that all related circuits are dead; 
e) The work should be done by or under supervision of a competent person; 
f) There should be a second person competent in the treatment of electric shock; 
g) A person doing a job should have his/her hands, clothing is dry, should not stay on wet deck or in the water, rain; 
h) A person working with electric equipment should not wear metal wrist watches, bracelets; 
i) If working with live equipment additional precautions should be observed: working position should be safe and secured to avoid accidental contact with the live parts, contact with bear metal should be avoided, insulated gloves should be worn; 
j) Improvised repairs to electrical equipment must be avoided.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="2">
      <my:Description>Remote starts</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Post a notice at the equipment controls that maintenance/repairs is carried out; 
b) Fuses or circuits should be reconnected by a person who disconnected them or under direct order of such a person</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
